                       "message":  "EGUIHOST-TEST-EXTRACTION: extract menu_tests to a sibling file, retire split-exemption\n\nPer the 2026-06-03 post-menu-arc deep audit\u0027s flagged follow-up (and the host.rs\nprecedent): the inline #[cfg(test)] mod menu_tests (~120L) pushed\neditor-egui-host/src/lib.rs past the §1.3 Rule 3 1000-line split cap in #299, which\ncarried a // SPLIT-EXEMPTION: annotation in-the-moment. This extracts that module\nverbatim to a sibling src/menu_tests.rs (declared `#[cfg(test)] mod menu_tests;`),\ndropping lib.rs from 1045L to 915L and RETIRING the split-exemption annotation.\n\nBehaviour-identical: same module path (`super` is the crate root either way), same\n8 tests, byte-identical assertions (dedented only). No production-logic change.\n\n- crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs: 1045 -\u003e 915L; inline `mod menu_tests {...}` -\u003e\n  `#[cfg(test)] mod menu_tests;`; SPLIT-EXEMPTION block removed.\n- crates/editor-egui-host/src/menu_tests.rs: NEW (130L) - the extracted module + a\n  header doc-comment.\n\ncargo check + fmt clean; all 8 menu tests pass; split-exemption lint now PASSes\nWITHOUT an annotation (lib.rs 915L). No Cargo.toml change.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
