                       "message":  "EGUIHOST-TEST-EXTRACTION: drop literal SPLIT-EXEMPTION marker from menu_tests doc\n\nCodex review of 06a18cd: the new menu_tests.rs header doc comment contained the\nexact literal `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:` substring (describing the annotation it\nretires). The split-exemption lint matches that substring ANYWHERE in a .rs file,\nso it would (a) falsely auto-exempt menu_tests.rs if it ever crossed 1000L and\n(b) leave a live marker hit in the very crate this PR was meant to clear.\nReworded to \"prior line-cap split annotation\" — no literal marker. A\n`grep -rn SPLIT-EXEMPTION` over editor-egui-host/src is now ZERO. Doc-comment\nonly; behaviour-identical.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
